> Why did the chicken cross the road? In this case, it's definitely to get to the mustard on the other side, because, boy, do those two make a mean combination! This mustard means business – particularly when you add the extra mustard seeds.

Boil a #large pot{} of water with @salt{1/4%tsp}. Chop the green leafy part from the @leeks{2} and discard. Slice the leeks in half lengthways and then very thinly slice widthways (discarding the little root on the end). Peel the @potatoes{2} and chop into 4cm cubes. Put the potatoes in the #pot{} of boiling water and cook for roughly ~{20%minutes}.

> The potatoes are cooked when you can easily slip a knife through them.

Bring another pot of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} and cut the tops and bottoms off the @green beans{2}(topped and tailed) (this is called top and tailing!). Cook them in the boiling water for ~{3%minutes}, when 3 mins are up drain the green beans and run cold water through them to stop them cooking further. Set aside.

Put @oil{2%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} on medium heat and add the leeks to the pan with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and a grind of @ground black pepper{grind}. Cook for about ~{5%minutes} until soft and then transfer the leeks to a #plate{}.

Season the @British chicken breasts{4} with a pinch of @salt{pinch} and some @black pepper{}. Add @oil{2%tbsp} to the pan your leeks were in (no need to wash!), keeping it on medium heat. Cook for ~{7%minutes} on one side and then turn over and cook for another ~{7%minutes} on the other side, until the outside is brown and the inside is cooked.

> The chicken is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

When your chicken is cooked, add the @double cream{1} to the pan along with the @cider & horseradish wholegrain mustard{1.5%tbsp}, leeks and @water{2%tbsp}, stir. Cook for another ~{3%minutes} until everything is nicely combined and hot. Spoon a little of the creamy mixture over your chicken and set the pan aside to rest, covering the pan with a #lid{} or some #tin foil{} to keep the chicken warm.

When your potatoes are cooked, drain them, pop them back into the pot with @salt{1/4%tsp}, a good grind of @black pepper{grind}, @?butter{1%tbsp} and @?milk{2%tbsp} and mash with a #potato masher{}. Pop a lid on the pot and set aside for ~{2%minutes}.

Put @oil{2%tbsp} in a frying pan with the @mustard seeds{1%tsp} and wait for ~{30%seconds} until they start to splutter.

> Don't leave the mustard seeds alone in the pan for too long or the mustard seeds will start jumping out!

Add your green beans, a good pinch of @salt{pinch} and some @pepper{} and stir-fry for about ~{2%minutes} until your beans are hot.

When everything is ready, stir @water{1%tbsp} into your creamy chicken sauce if the liquid has evaporated too much. Take your chicken breasts out of the pan and slice them into 2cm slices. Serve your chicken with your mash, your stir-fried beans and a good dollop of sauce. Enjoy!